  "title": "CHEF",
  "description": "<p>Neighbourhood foodshop requires a Chief Cook specialising in local cuisine.</p><p>The employee is required to work <strong>split shifts</strong> (5.00am–9.00am and 4.00pm–8.00pm), including <strong>weekends and public holidays</strong>.</p><p>Duties include food preparation and cooking in accordance with <strong>food hygiene and safety standards</strong>, supervising and training assistants, and coordinating with counter staff to ensure smooth operations.</p><p>The employee is also responsible for <strong>inventory control</strong>, ensuring sufficient stock of ingredients at all times\nwithout overstocking, particularly perishable items.</p><p>The candidate must have <strong>at least three (3) years of relevant working experience</strong> and be able to work well as part of a team.</p>",
